node.text: Working in restaurants, Lan Lam learned a ton of useful information, including how to open beer with pretty much anything.

node.title: How to Open Beer with Anything 🍺

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by America's Test Kitchen on September 06, 2021. May be an image of pizza.

node.text: Lasagna purists might be surprised to find that we swapped some traditional ingredients for more flavorful (trust us) ingredients, such as cottage cheese, fontina, and parmesan. Our members call it “a keeper” and “the BEST lasagna I’ve ever tasted.” Cheese and Tomato Lasagna recipe link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by America's Test Kitchen on September 06, 2021. May be an image of food and indoor.

node.text: To make grilled cauliflower with a tender interior and a flavorful, nicely browned exterior, we first microwaved it until it was cooked through and then briefly grilled it to pick up color and flavor. Grilled Cauliflower recipe link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by America's Test Kitchen on September 06, 2021. May be an image of dessert.

node.text: Ice cream flavors abound, but chocolate remains a perennial favorite. We wanted to find out which chocolate ice cream reigns supreme. Read our Chocolate Ice Cream taste test by clicking the link in our profile.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by America's Test Kitchen on September 06, 2021. May be an image of dessert.

node.text: “PERFECT!!! Just perfect! No leftovers in our family.” - Natalia S., web member. Get our Apple Strudel recipe by clicking the link in our profile.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by America's Test Kitchen on September 05, 2021. May be an image of pasta.

node.text: You already know ragu rosso, the king of ragu sauces. But perhaps you haven't met the queen: ragu bianco, which, in our version, trades the tomato for lemon and cream. Pork, Fennel, and Lemon Ragu with Pappardelle recipe link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by America's Test Kitchen on September 05, 2021. May be an image of food.

node.text: If you enjoy chicken piccata or a bagel with the works, you already know that bright, briny capers can be transformative. Because capers can be stored in the refrigerator for months and added to a dish straight from the jar, they are both easy and convenient to use. But other parts of the plant—the berries and the leaves—are equally vibrant. We purchased several jars of both, compared the flavors and textures of the different products, and tried each in a few applications. Sign up for a free trial for our testing results. Link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by America's Test Kitchen on September 05, 2021. May be an image of food.

node.text: Eaten as a hearty side or a light vegetarian main, whole braised cauliflower is becoming increasingly popular, and for good reason: Not only is the dish a showstopper, it's also healthy and tastes great. Get our recipe for a Whole Pot-Roasted Cauliflower with Tomatoes and Olives recipe by clicking the link in our profile.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by America's Test Kitchen on September 05, 2021. May be an image of dessert and indoor.

node.text: This classic ATK recipe for sticky buns is a family favorite for a sweet weekend brunch treat. Recipe link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by America's Test Kitchen on September 04, 2021. May be an image of food.

node.text: The popularity of this ancient spice has recently skyrocketed. For the most vibrant color and best flavor, which turmeric is best? Sign up for a free trial for our ground turmeric taste test.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by America's Test Kitchen on September 04, 2021. May be an image of food.

node.text: An ingredient from Switzerland—not Italy—takes this classic to a new level. Tagliatelle with Prosciutto and Peas recipe link in bio.

node.text: This classic Iranian dish takes rice to a whole other level, with perfectly plump, separate grains and a crispy, buttery, nutty-tasting crust. Chelow recipe link in bio.

node.text: Swordfish is a favorite fish to grill along the Mediterranean and beyond. Get our Grilled Swordfish Skewers with Tomato-Scallion Caponata recipe by clicking the link in our profile.
